                        <interp inst="t18520223-name-95" type="given" value="JOHN"></interp>JOHN NEWELL</persName>
                  </hi> (<hi rend="italic">policeman, R</hi> 340). I produce a certificate—(<hi rend="italic">read—Central Criminal Court; William Smith, convicted on his own confession, Aug. 1850, of stealing boots; confined six months</hi>)—I was present, the prisoner is the person—there were two other cases against him; but he was not tried upon them. <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <rs id="t18520223-296-verdict-1" type="verdictDescription">
